{"parentUuid":"37821a7c-d94f-4975-856c-74134a0fc0e9","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"23933e0c-9ea3-4daf-8e03-240f8e5e55d7","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01H8tLdP4AFfGqP4akvPCH17","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Grep found zero `XCTAssert*`/`XCTUnwrap`/`XCTFail`/`XCTestCase`/`import XCTest` matches (exit 1 = no matches). All five files are converted.\n\n## Per-file report\n\n| File | Suite kind | `@Test` count |\n|---|---|---|\n| `AppDataExportTests.swift` | `@Suite struct` | 7 |\n| `AppDataImportTests.swift` | `@Suite struct` | 11 |\n| `AppDataRoundTripTests.swift` | `@Suite struct` | 4 |\n| `AppStatePersistedFormatTests.swift` | `@Suite struct` | 8 |\n| `AppPersistenceTests.swift` | `@Suite struct` | 6 |\n\n## Decisions and notes\n\n- **All five chose plain `@Suite struct`.** None of the files had `setUp`/`setUpWithError`/`tearDown`/`tearDownWithError`, and none touch shared/process-wide state: every test operates on freshly-constructed in-memory `AppState` values and encodes/decodes to in-memory `Data`. There is no file I/O to shared locations and no `UserDefaults`/`AppUserDefaults` access (notably `AppDataExport.suggestedFilename` is called with explicit `calendar:`/`timeZone:` args, so it doesn't read process locale state). So `.serialized` was not required.\n- **Added `import Foundation`** to all five — they use `Data`, `Date`, `DateComponents`, `Calendar`, `TimeZone` but none previously imported it (it came transitively via XCTest). Kept `import MovieSwiftFluxCore` and the full `#if os(tvOS)/macOS/else` `@testable import` block exactly as-is (this block has a tvOS branch too, which I preserved).\n- **`throws` tests:** kept `throws` on every test that originally had it (all the ones using `try`). The three `XCTAssertThrowsError` blocks were converted but their enclosing tests do NOT need `throws` because the `try` calls now live inside `do/catch` — I left their signatures exactly matching the originals (`decodeEnvelopeRejectsUnsupportedFormatVersion` kept `throws` since it has a top-level `try AppDataExport.data(...)`; `decodeEnvelopeWrapsCorruptDataInDecodeFailedError`, `decodeRejectsFormatVersionFromAFutureBuild`-had-throws, and `decodeWrapsCorruptDataInDecodeFailedError`-no-throws preserved as original).\n\n## One translation choice worth flagging\n\nThe four `XCTAssertThrowsError(try expr) { error in guard case ... else { XCTFail; return } ... }` blocks inspect the specific error case (and one also asserts on an associated value). I converted these to **`do { _ = try expr; Issue.record(...) } catch { guard case ... else { Issue.record(...); return }; #expect(...) }`** rather than `#expect(throws:)`, because the original logic both pattern-matches a specific enum case with associated-value binding and (in two cases) asserts on the bound value. The do/catch form preserves that exact intent, including recording a failure if no error is thrown (which the original `XCTAssertThrowsError` did implicitly). This is the spec's \"wrap in do/catch with `Issue.record`\" path. No assertion meaning changed.\n\nPer instructions, I did not build (sibling files in the target are still mid-migration)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab20dd753072c0423 (use SendMessage with to: 'ab20dd753072c0423' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 60599\ntool_uses: 13\nduration_ms: 173990</usage>"}]}]},"uuid":"9b9a263e-c816-4c5d-baf2-2273de7374bd","timestamp":"2026-05-26T05:07:00.790Z","toolUseResult":{"status":"completed","prompt":"You are migrating FIVE Swift test files from XCTest to the Swift Testing framework, part of a larger careful migration in the MovieSwiftUI project. Do NOT change test logic or assertion meaning — this is a framework translation only.\n\nFILES TO CONVERT (rewrite each in place), all under /Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui/MovieSwift/MovieSwiftTests/ :\n- AppDataExportTests.swift\n- AppDataImportTests.swift\n- AppDataRoundTripTests.swift\n- AppStatePersistedFormatTests.swift\n- AppPersistenceTests.swift\n\nGOLD-STANDARD EXAMPLES already converted in this repo (read them first to match style exactly):\n- /Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui/MovieSwift/Packages/MovieSwiftFluxCore/Tests/MovieSwiftFluxCoreTests/ModelUtilityTests.swift  (plain `@Suite struct`)\n- /Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui/MovieSwift/Packages/Backend/Tests/BackendTests/APIKeyProviderTests.swift  (`@Suite(.serialized) final class` with init/deinit for setup/teardown)\n\nCONVERSION RULES:\n1. Replace `import XCTest` with `import Testing`. KEEP all other imports (e.g. `import Foundation`, `import MovieSwiftFluxCore`, and the `#if os(macOS) @testable import Film_O_Matic #else @testable import MovieSwift #endif` block — keep that exactly). If a file uses Foundation types (Data, Date, URL, FileManager, Bundle) and does not already `import Foundation`, ADD `import Foundation`.\n2. Class → suite:\n   - If the class has NO setUp/tearDown: `final class XTests: XCTestCase {` → `@Suite struct XTests {`.\n   - If the class HAS setUp/setUpWithError or tearDown/tearDownWithError: convert to `@Suite(.serialized) final class XTests {` and move setUp logic into `init()` (or `init() throws` if it throws) and tearDown logic into `deinit`. DROP the `super.setUp()`/`super.tearDown()` calls. Stored properties that setUp assigned become regular stored properties initialized in `init`. (These persistence tests typically create/cleanup temp directories or snapshot UserDefaults — that's shared/file-system state, so `.serialized` is required to be safe under Swift Testing's default parallelism.)\n   - IMPORTANT: if a suite does file I/O to shared/default locations, touches `UserDefaults`/`AppUserDefaults`, or otherwise uses process-wide state, it MUST be `@Suite(.serialized)`. When unsure, use `.serialized` (it's always safe, just slower). Do NOT add `@MainActor` to any of these files.\n3. `func testFoo()` → `@Test func foo()` (drop leading `test`, keep the rest). Add `throws` if the original method was `throws` or used `try XCTUnwrap`. Add `async` only if the body genuinely awaits (these don't).\n4. Assertion mapping (translate EVERY assertion), splitting on the TOP-LEVEL comma respecting nested brackets/strings:\n   - `XCTAssertEqual(a, b)` → `#expect(a == b)`   (with message: `#expect(a == b, \"msg\")`)\n   - `XCTAssertNotEqual(a, b)` → `#expect(a != b)`\n   - `XCTAssertNil(x)` → `#expect(x == nil)`\n   - `XCTAssertNotNil(x)` → `#expect(x != nil)`\n   - `XCTAssertTrue(x)` → `#expect(x)`  ;  `XCTAssertFalse(x)` → `#expect(!(x))`\n   - `XCTAssertGreaterThan(a,b)`→`#expect(a > b)`; `...GreaterThanOrEqual`→`>=`; `...LessThan`→`<`; `...LessThanOrEqual`→`<=`\n   - `try XCTUnwrap(x)` → `try #require(x)`  (ensure the test is `throws`)\n   - `XCTFail(\"msg\")` → `Issue.record(\"msg\")`\n   - `XCTAssertThrowsError(try expr) { error in ... }` → `#expect(throws: (any Error).self) { try expr }` if it only checks that it throws; if it inspects the error, use `let error = #expect(throws: SomeError.self) { try expr }` or wrap in do/catch with `Issue.record`. Match the original intent; if a specific error type/case is checked, prefer `#expect(throws:)` or a do/catch + `#expect`.\n   - `XCTAssertNoThrow(try expr)` → just `try expr` inside a `throws` test (or `#expect(throws: Never.self) { try expr }`).\n   - When the LHS uses `??` or other low-precedence operators, parenthesize it before `==`, e.g. `#expect((a ?? []) == b)`.\n5. Keep ALL helper methods, nested types, comments, and `// MARK:` lines exactly as-is.\n\nAfter rewriting each file, self-review: zero `XCTAssert*`/`XCTUnwrap`/`XCTFail`/`XCTestCase` remain; starts with `import Testing`; suites are `@Suite struct` or `@Suite(.serialized) final class`; every test has `@Test`. Do NOT build (the target won't compile until sibling files are migrated too). Report back per file: suite kind chosen (struct vs serialized class) and number of `@Test` methods, plus any file where you were unsure about parallel-safety or an assertion translation.","agentId":"ab20dd753072c0423","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Grep found zero `XCTAssert*`/`XCTUnwrap`/`XCTFail`/`XCTestCase`/`import XCTest` matches (exit 1 = no matches). All five files are converted.\n\n## Per-file report\n\n| File | Suite kind | `@Test` count |\n|---|---|---|\n| `AppDataExportTests.swift` | `@Suite struct` | 7 |\n| `AppDataImportTests.swift` | `@Suite struct` | 11 |\n| `AppDataRoundTripTests.swift` | `@Suite struct` | 4 |\n| `AppStatePersistedFormatTests.swift` | `@Suite struct` | 8 |\n| `AppPersistenceTests.swift` | `@Suite struct` | 6 |\n\n## Decisions and notes\n\n- **All five chose plain `@Suite struct`.** None of the files had `setUp`/`setUpWithError`/`tearDown`/`tearDownWithError`, and none touch shared/process-wide state: every test operates on freshly-constructed in-memory `AppState` values and encodes/decodes to in-memory `Data`. There is no file I/O to shared locations and no `UserDefaults`/`AppUserDefaults` access (notably `AppDataExport.suggestedFilename` is called with explicit `calendar:`/`timeZone:` args, so it doesn't read process locale state). So `.serialized` was not required.\n- **Added `import Foundation`** to all five — they use `Data`, `Date`, `DateComponents`, `Calendar`, `TimeZone` but none previously imported it (it came transitively via XCTest). Kept `import MovieSwiftFluxCore` and the full `#if os(tvOS)/macOS/else` `@testable import` block exactly as-is (this block has a tvOS branch too, which I preserved).\n- **`throws` tests:** kept `throws` on every test that originally had it (all the ones using `try`). The three `XCTAssertThrowsError` blocks were converted but their enclosing tests do NOT need `throws` because the `try` calls now live inside `do/catch` — I left their signatures exactly matching the originals (`decodeEnvelopeRejectsUnsupportedFormatVersion` kept `throws` since it has a top-level `try AppDataExport.data(...)`; `decodeEnvelopeWrapsCorruptDataInDecodeFailedError`, `decodeRejectsFormatVersionFromAFutureBuild`-had-throws, and `decodeWrapsCorruptDataInDecodeFailedError`-no-throws preserved as original).\n\n## One translation choice worth flagging\n\nThe four `XCTAssertThrowsError(try expr) { error in guard case ... else { XCTFail; return } ... }` blocks inspect the specific error case (and one also asserts on an associated value). I converted these to **`do { _ = try expr; Issue.record(...) } catch { guard case ... else { Issue.record(...); return }; #expect(...) }`** rather than `#expect(throws:)`, because the original logic both pattern-matches a specific enum case with associated-value binding and (in two cases) asserts on the bound value. The do/catch form preserves that exact intent, including recording a failure if no error is thrown (which the original `XCTAssertThrowsError` did implicitly). This is the spec's \"wrap in do/catch with `Issue.record`\" path. No assertion meaning changed.\n\nPer instructions, I did not build (sibling files in the target are still mid-migration)."}],"totalDurationMs":173990,"totalTokens":60599,"totalToolUseCount":13,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":489,"cache_read_input_tokens":58933,"output_tokens":1175,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":489},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1175,"cache_read_input_tokens":58933,"cache_creation_input_tokens":489,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":489,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"toolStats":{"readCount":7,"searchCount":0,"bashCount":1,"editFileCount":5,"linesAdded":1013,"linesRemoved":0,"otherToolCount":0}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"37821a7c-d94f-4975-856c-74134a0fc0e9","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"feat/swift-testing-migration","slug":"snuggly-shimmying-pebble"}
{"parentUuid":"1f3aa543-7d39-49c4-935b-818bb3f1f999","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"23933e0c-9ea3-4daf-8e03-240f8e5e55d7","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XqToBpNw3KwcfVHCpQtBM9","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All five files converted successfully. Self-review passed: zero `XCTAssert*`/`XCTUnwrap`/`XCTFail`/`XCTestCase`/`import XCTest` remain, each starts with `import Testing`, and every test is `@Test`.\n\n## Per-file report\n\n**CrashReportStoreTests.swift** — `@Suite(.serialized) final class`, 15 `@Test` methods.\n- Had `setUpWithError`/`tearDownWithError` → moved to `init()`/`deinit` (dropped `super.*`). Per the task's explicit guidance, treated crash-report file I/O as needing `.serialized`.\n- Added `import Foundation` (uses Data, Date, URL, FileManager, Calendar, TimeZone, UUID, DateComponents).\n- `XCTAssertThrowsError(...) { ... }` with a `guard case ... else { XCTFail }` block became `#expect { try ... } throws: { error in ... }` returning `Bool`, with `XCTFail` → `Issue.record`.\n- `try XCTUnwrap` → `try #require`; `XCTAssertLessThan` → `<`; equality/nil/prefix assertions mapped per rules.\n\n**AppDataICloudBackupTests.swift** — `@Suite(.serialized) final class`, 11 `@Test` methods.\n- `setUpWithError` (creates temp dir, `try`) → `init() throws`; teardown → `deinit`.\n- Added `import Foundation` (Data, URL, FileManager, UUID); kept `import MovieSwiftFluxCore`.\n- Two `XCTAssertThrowsError` blocks converted to `#expect { } throws: { }`; `XCTAssertFalse(x)` → `#expect(!(x))`; `XCTAssertGreaterThanOrEqual` → `>=`; `try XCTUnwrap` → `try #require`.\n\n**MovieSpotlightIndexerTests.swift** — `@Suite struct`, 7 `@Test` methods. Pure logic, no setUp/teardown. Kept `import MovieSwiftFluxCore`; no Foundation types used directly, so none added. Helper `makeMovie` preserved.\n\n**OnboardingFlowTests.swift** — `@Suite struct`, 17 `@Test` methods. Pure logic, no AppUserDefaults mutation (so plain struct, not `.serialized`). `XCTAssertFalse(x)` → `#expect(!(x))`, including the multi-line `shouldShow(...)` calls wrapped as `!(...)`.\n\n**MoviesListLoadingStateTests.swift** — `@Suite struct`, 16 `@Test` methods. Pure logic. Kept `import Backend` and `import MovieSwiftFluxCore`. The final test's `if case .failed { } else { XCTFail }` had only the `XCTFail` → `Issue.record`, control-flow preserved exactly. Nested `struct StubError: Error {}` kept as-is.\n\n### Notes / uncertainty\n- For the `XCTAssertThrowsError` cases (3 total, in CrashReportStore + AppDataICloudBackup) the originals inspect the error via `guard case ... else { XCTFail }`. I used the `#expect { } throws: { error in ... }` form returning `Bool` (true on match, `Issue.record` + false on mismatch) rather than the simpler `#expect(throws: (any Error).self)`, since the originals specifically assert the error *case* — this preserves assertion meaning faithfully.\n- CrashReportStore/AppDataICloudBackup each use a unique per-test temp dir, so they're arguably isolated enough for a plain struct. Per the task's explicit instruction to treat these as `.serialized` (and because they had setUp/tearDown), I used `@Suite(.serialized) final class`.\n- As instructed, did not build. No `@MainActor` added anywhere."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a97827138678988fe (use SendMessage with to: 'a97827138678988fe' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 59315\ntool_uses: 15\nduration_ms: 218200</usage>"}]}]},"uuid":"1364a451-e747-433d-90c6-220e0cec3963","timestamp":"2026-05-26T05:08:03.054Z","toolUseResult":{"status":"completed","prompt":"You are migrating FIVE Swift test files from XCTest to the Swift Testing framework, part of a larger careful migration in the MovieSwiftUI project. Do NOT change test logic or assertion meaning — this is a framework translation only.\n\nFILES TO CONVERT (rewrite each in place), all under /Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui/MovieSwift/MovieSwiftTests/ :\n- CrashReportStoreTests.swift\n- AppDataICloudBackupTests.swift\n- MovieSpotlightIndexerTests.swift\n- OnboardingFlowTests.swift\n- MoviesListLoadingStateTests.swift\n\nGOLD-STANDARD EXAMPLES already converted in this repo (read them first to match style exactly):\n- /Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui/MovieSwift/Packages/MovieSwiftFluxCore/Tests/MovieSwiftFluxCoreTests/ModelUtilityTests.swift  (plain `@Suite struct`)\n- /Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui/MovieSwift/Packages/Backend/Tests/BackendTests/APIKeyProviderTests.swift  (`@Suite(.serialized) final class` with init/deinit)\n\nCONVERSION RULES:\n1. Replace `import XCTest` with `import Testing`. KEEP all other imports (e.g. `import Foundation`, `import MovieSwiftFluxCore`, `import Backend`, and any `#if os(macOS) @testable import Film_O_Matic #else @testable import MovieSwift #endif` block — keep exactly). If a file uses Foundation types (Data, Date, URL, FileManager, Bundle, Calendar, TimeZone) and does not already `import Foundation`, ADD `import Foundation`. Keep any `#if !os(tvOS)` / `#if os(...)` guards exactly as-is.\n2. Class → suite:\n   - No setUp/tearDown: `final class XTests: XCTestCase {` → `@Suite struct XTests {`.\n   - Has setUp/tearDown (incl. `setUpWithError`/`tearDownWithError`): `@Suite(.serialized) final class XTests {` with setUp logic in `init()`/`init() throws` and tearDown logic in `deinit`. DROP `super.setUp()`/`super.tearDown()`. Stored properties assigned in setUp become stored properties set in `init`.\n   - File I/O to shared/default locations, or any process-wide/global state (UserDefaults, singletons) → MUST be `@Suite(.serialized)`. When unsure, use `.serialized`. Do NOT add `@MainActor` to any of these files.\n   - CrashReportStoreTests and AppDataICloudBackupTests do crash-report / iCloud-backup file I/O — treat as needing `.serialized` unless every test clearly uses a unique per-test temp directory (in which case a plain struct is fine; match what the existing setUp/temp-dir code does).\n3. `func testFoo()` → `@Test func foo()` (drop leading `test`). Add `throws` if original was `throws` or used `try XCTUnwrap`. Add `async` only if the body genuinely awaits (these likely don't).\n4. Assertion mapping (translate EVERY assertion), splitting on the TOP-LEVEL comma respecting nested brackets/strings:\n   - `XCTAssertEqual(a, b)` → `#expect(a == b)` (msg → second arg)\n   - `XCTAssertNotEqual(a, b)` → `#expect(a != b)`\n   - `XCTAssertNil(x)` → `#expect(x == nil)` ; `XCTAssertNotNil(x)` → `#expect(x != nil)`\n   - `XCTAssertTrue(x)` → `#expect(x)` ; `XCTAssertFalse(x)` → `#expect(!(x))`\n   - `XCTAssertGreaterThan`→`>`, `...GreaterThanOrEqual`→`>=`, `...LessThan`→`<`, `...LessThanOrEqual`→`<=`\n   - `try XCTUnwrap(x)` → `try #require(x)` (test must be `throws`)\n   - `XCTFail(\"msg\")` → `Issue.record(\"msg\")`\n   - `XCTAssertThrowsError(try expr)` → `#expect(throws: (any Error).self) { try expr }` (or specific error type if the original inspects it / `do{}catch{}` with `#expect`). `XCTAssertNoThrow(try expr)` → `try expr` in a throws test.\n   - Parenthesize low-precedence LHS before `==`: `#expect((a ?? []) == b)`.\n5. Keep ALL helper methods, nested types, comments, `// MARK:` lines exactly as-is.\n\nNote: OnboardingFlowTests and MovieSpotlightIndexerTests and MoviesListLoadingStateTests are pure-logic (no file I/O, no global mutation) → plain `@Suite struct`. (If OnboardingFlowTests mutates AppUserDefaults anywhere, use `.serialized`.)\n\nAfter rewriting each file, self-review: zero `XCTAssert*`/`XCTUnwrap`/`XCTFail`/`XCTestCase` remain; starts with `import Testing`; correct suite kind; every test `@Test`. Do NOT build. Report back per file: suite kind chosen and number of `@Test` methods, plus any uncertainty.","agentId":"a97827138678988fe","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All five files converted successfully. Self-review passed: zero `XCTAssert*`/`XCTUnwrap`/`XCTFail`/`XCTestCase`/`import XCTest` remain, each starts with `import Testing`, and every test is `@Test`.\n\n## Per-file report\n\n**CrashReportStoreTests.swift** — `@Suite(.serialized) final class`, 15 `@Test` methods.\n- Had `setUpWithError`/`tearDownWithError` → moved to `init()`/`deinit` (dropped `super.*`). Per the task's explicit guidance, treated crash-report file I/O as needing `.serialized`.\n- Added `import Foundation` (uses Data, Date, URL, FileManager, Calendar, TimeZone, UUID, DateComponents).\n- `XCTAssertThrowsError(...) { ... }` with a `guard case ... else { XCTFail }` block became `#expect { try ... } throws: { error in ... }` returning `Bool`, with `XCTFail` → `Issue.record`.\n- `try XCTUnwrap` → `try #require`; `XCTAssertLessThan` → `<`; equality/nil/prefix assertions mapped per rules.\n\n**AppDataICloudBackupTests.swift** — `@Suite(.serialized) final class`, 11 `@Test` methods.\n- `setUpWithError` (creates temp dir, `try`) → `init() throws`; teardown → `deinit`.\n- Added `import Foundation` (Data, URL, FileManager, UUID); kept `import MovieSwiftFluxCore`.\n- Two `XCTAssertThrowsError` blocks converted to `#expect { } throws: { }`; `XCTAssertFalse(x)` → `#expect(!(x))`; `XCTAssertGreaterThanOrEqual` → `>=`; `try XCTUnwrap` → `try #require`.\n\n**MovieSpotlightIndexerTests.swift** — `@Suite struct`, 7 `@Test` methods. Pure logic, no setUp/teardown. Kept `import MovieSwiftFluxCore`; no Foundation types used directly, so none added. Helper `makeMovie` preserved.\n\n**OnboardingFlowTests.swift** — `@Suite struct`, 17 `@Test` methods. Pure logic, no AppUserDefaults mutation (so plain struct, not `.serialized`). `XCTAssertFalse(x)` → `#expect(!(x))`, including the multi-line `shouldShow(...)` calls wrapped as `!(...)`.\n\n**MoviesListLoadingStateTests.swift** — `@Suite struct`, 16 `@Test` methods. Pure logic. Kept `import Backend` and `import MovieSwiftFluxCore`. The final test's `if case .failed { } else { XCTFail }` had only the `XCTFail` → `Issue.record`, control-flow preserved exactly. Nested `struct StubError: Error {}` kept as-is.\n\n### Notes / uncertainty\n- For the `XCTAssertThrowsError` cases (3 total, in CrashReportStore + AppDataICloudBackup) the originals inspect the error via `guard case ... else { XCTFail }`. I used the `#expect { } throws: { error in ... }` form returning `Bool` (true on match, `Issue.record` + false on mismatch) rather than the simpler `#expect(throws: (any Error).self)`, since the originals specifically assert the error *case* — this preserves assertion meaning faithfully.\n- CrashReportStore/AppDataICloudBackup each use a unique per-test temp dir, so they're arguably isolated enough for a plain struct. Per the task's explicit instruction to treat these as `.serialized` (and because they had setUp/tearDown), I used `@Suite(.serialized) final class`.\n- As instructed, did not build. No `@MainActor` added anywhere."}],"totalDurationMs":218200,"totalTokens":59315,"totalToolUseCount":15,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":664,"cache_read_input_tokens":57324,"output_tokens":1325,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":664},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1325,"cache_read_input_tokens":57324,"cache_creation_input_tokens":664,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":664,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"toolStats":{"readCount":7,"searchCount":0,"bashCount":2,"editFileCount":5,"linesAdded":918,"linesRemoved":0,"otherToolCount":1}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"1f3aa543-7d39-49c4-935b-818bb3f1f999","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"feat/swift-testing-migration","slug":"snuggly-shimmying-pebble"}
