{"parentUuid":"e4d9bc67-c419-4e83-9e13-290c4ba7b201","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01PYj53LkQgsPfo9LkRDDdVC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Clear split: `MovieDetailStateTests`/`MoviesMenuListPageListenerTests`/`AppBootstrapTests`/`MovieSwiftTests` are synchronous `@MainActor` suites (delegatable); `PeopleActionsTests` is async (42 expectations — I'll handle it with the same continuation-bridge pattern). Let me delegate the sync `@MainActor` files to two subagents (the 2277-line `MovieSwiftTests` gets its own), using `ErrorDiagnosticTests` as the `@MainActor struct` gold example."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1751,"cache_read_input_tokens":761183,"output_tokens":5027,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1751,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":5027,"cache_read_input_tokens":761183,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1751,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1751},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CbQc7hj2w8czfZGVmt8x4","attributionMcpServer":"ccd_session","attributionMcpTool":"mark_chapter","type":"assistant","uuid":"413a9feb-1ac1-4e77-aa22-983dd7d954e3","timestamp":"2026-05-26T05:12:10.286Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"feat/swift-testing-migration","slug":"snuggly-shimmying-pebble"}
{"parentUuid":"413a9feb-1ac1-4e77-aa22-983dd7d954e3","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01PYj53LkQgsPfo9LkRDDdVC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01MMvR7bujk5P6rqvceZ2tt4","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Convert 3 MainActor app test files","subagent_type":"general-purpose","run_in_background":true,"prompt":"Migrate THREE Swift test files from XCTest to Swift Testing, part of a careful migration in MovieSwiftUI. Do NOT change test logic or assertion meaning — framework translation only.\n\nFILES (rewrite each in place), under /Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui/MovieSwift/MovieSwiftTests/ :\n- MovieDetailStateTests.swift\n- MoviesMenuListPageListenerTests.swift\n- AppBootstrapTests.swift\n\nGOLD-STANDARD @MainActor EXAMPLE (read it first to match style):\n/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui/MovieSwift/MovieSwiftTests/ErrorDiagnosticTests.swift  (already converted: `@Suite @MainActor struct`)\n\nThese three suites are all currently `@MainActor final class XTests: XCTestCase`. They exercise main-actor app code (view-presentation helpers, a @MainActor page listener, app-launch bootstrap). They are SYNCHRONOUS (no expectation/waitForExpectations, no XCTUnwrap, no XCTFail, no async).\n\nRULES:\n1. `import XCTest` → `import Testing`. Add `import Foundation` if the file uses Foundation types (Date, Data, etc.) and doesn't already import it. KEEP `import MovieSwiftFluxCore`/`import Backend` and the `#if os(tvOS) @testable import MovieSwiftTV #elseif os(macOS) @testable import Film_O_Matic #else @testable import MovieSwift #endif` block EXACTLY (note: MoviesMenuListPageListenerTests is wrapped in `#if !os(tvOS)` ... `#endif` — preserve that outer guard).\n2. Suite: `@MainActor final class XTests: XCTestCase {` → `@Suite @MainActor` on its own line(s) above `struct XTests {`. Keep the existing explanatory `// @MainActor:` comment if present. None of these have setUp/tearDown, so a struct is correct. Do NOT add `.serialized` (a @MainActor suite already runs serially on the main actor).\n3. `func testFoo() { ... }` → `@Test func foo() { ... }` (drop leading `test`). Keep `throws` only if a method already had it (none should need it). Do NOT add `async`.\n4. Assertions (split on TOP-LEVEL comma respecting nested brackets/strings):\n   - `XCTAssertEqual(a, b)` → `#expect(a == b)` (message → 2nd arg)\n   - `XCTAssertNotEqual(a, b)` → `#expect(a != b)`\n   - `XCTAssertNil(x)` → `#expect(x == nil)` ; `XCTAssertNotNil(x)` → `#expect(x != nil)`\n   - `XCTAssertTrue(x)` → `#expect(x)` ; `XCTAssertFalse(x)` → `#expect(!(x))`\n   - `XCTAssertGreaterThan`→`>`, `…GreaterThanOrEqual`→`>=`, `…LessThan`→`<`, `…LessThanOrEqual`→`<=`\n   - `XCTAssertIdentical(a,b)`→`#expect(a === b)`; `XCTAssertEqual` of object identity stays as written.\n   - Parenthesize `??`/low-precedence LHS before `==`: `#expect((a ?? x) == b)`.\n5. Keep ALL helper methods (e.g. `makeMovie`, `makePeople`, factory helpers), nested types, comments, and `// MARK:` lines exactly.\n\nAfter each file: confirm zero `XCTAssert*`/`XCTestCase`/`import XCTest` remain; `@Suite @MainActor struct`; every test `@Test`. Do NOT build (siblings still mid-migration). Report per file: number of `@Test` methods and any uncertainty."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1751,"cache_read_input_tokens":761183,"output_tokens":5027,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1751,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":5027,"cache_read_input_tokens":761183,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1751,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1751},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnosti