{"parentUuid":"0da863dc-f4e5-467d-866f-106a0e17be69","isSidechain":false,"attachment":{"type":"queued_command","prompt":"<task-notification>\n<task-id>a1913be728c0efd77</task-id>\n<tool-use-id>toolu_01MMvR7bujk5P6rqvceZ2tt4</tool-use-id>\n<output-file>/private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-scottdensmore-Developer-scottdensmore-movieswiftui/73bfc67d-407a-421c-bdf6-b48fa3a353d2/tasks/a1913be728c0efd77.output</output-file>\n<status>completed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Convert 3 MainActor app test files\" completed</summary>\n<result>All three files are fully migrated. Migration complete — framework translation only, no test logic or assertion meaning changed.\n\nPer-file results:\n\n**MovieDetailStateTests.swift** — 31 `@Test` methods\n- `@Suite @MainActor struct`, `import Testing`, kept the macOS/MovieSwift import block and `// @MainActor:` comment, both `makeMovie`/`makePeople` helpers, the static `focusSampleGroups`, all `// MARK:` lines, and nested-type references intact.\n- Notable translations: `XCTAssertNil(x)` → `#expect(x == nil)`, `XCTAssertNotEqual(a, c)` → `#expect(a != c)`, message-carrying asserts kept their string as the 2nd `#expect` arg, and the `for`-loop `XCTAssertEqual` → `#expect(... == ...)`.\n\n**MoviesMenuListPageListenerTests.swift** — 6 `@Test` methods\n- Preserved the outer `#if !os(tvOS)` ... `#endif` guard, all doc comments, the `// @MainActor:` comment. `XCTAssertNotNil(captured)` → `#expect(captured != nil)`.\n\n**AppBootstrapTests.swift** — 12 `@Test` methods\n- Kept the tvOS/macOS/MovieSwift import block, the `// @MainActor:` comment, all `// MARK:` sections, and the inline `#if DEBUG ... #else ... #endif` blocks inside test bodies (only the assertions inside them were translated).\n\nVerification: zero `XCTAssert*`, `XCTestCase`, or `import XCTest` remain in any of the three files (confirmed by full re-read). Each suite is `@Suite @MainActor struct` and every test is annotated `@Test`. No `.serialized` added, no `async`/`throws` added, and `import Foundation` was correctly NOT added since none of these files use Foundation types.\n\nNo uncertainties. For `XCTAssertTrue`/`XCTAssertFalse` I used `#expect(x)` and `#expect(!(x))` per the rules; the boolean expressions were already simple identifiers or single function calls so the extra parens around `!(...)` are harmless but match the spec exactly. As instructed, I did not build (sibling files are still mid-migration).</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>73542</total_tokens><tool_uses>29</tool_uses><duration_ms>233427</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>","commandMode":"task-notification"},"type":"attachment","uuid":"e3dc3742-bc1c-4ef0-9a75-1f52decfd751","timestamp":"2026-05-26T05:16:20.048Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"feat/swift-testing-migration","slug":"snuggly-shimmying-pebble"}
