{"parentUuid":"df581561-4deb-4026-8b4e-1f614f6770a0","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01L4i1FiQEe1RP1rmeF6oHyt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RzZeEty5JB3mgU9GCoQUqu","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\ntest(app): migrate MovieSwiftTests XCTest suites to Swift Testing\n\nConvert all 16 unit-test suites in the app target from XCTest to Swift\nTesting (XCUITest suites stay on XCTest — Swift Testing can't drive\nXCUIApplication). XCTAssert* → #expect, XCTUnwrap → #require, XCTFail →\nIssue.record, XCTAssertThrowsError → do/catch + Issue.record.\n\n- Pure-logic / in-memory suites → `@Suite struct`.\n- Suites exercising main-actor app code (MovieSwiftTests, MovieDetailState,\n  AppBootstrap, ErrorDiagnostic, MoviesMenuListPageListener) → `@Suite\n  @MainActor struct`.\n- Suites mutating shared global/file state (PeopleActionsTests swaps\n  APIService.shared; CrashReportStore / AppDataICloudBackup do file I/O\n  with setUp/tearDown) → `@Suite(.serialized) final class` with\n  init/deinit, since Swift Testing runs in parallel by default.\n- PeopleActionsTests' XCTestExpectation flows are rewritten as async\n  continuation bridges (collectDispatches until-match / fixed-window for\n  the inverted \"does not dispatch\" cases).\n- ErrorDiagnosticTests' XCTSkipUnless becomes an early return (no\n  mid-test skip in Swift Testing).\n\nAll three app test targets build clean; the 370 iOS unit tests pass.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\" 2>&1 | tail -2","description":"Commit app target Swift Testing conversion"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":960,"cache_read_input_tokens":834104,"output_tokens":673,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":